CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 7, 1966, pg. 1A, reads: "Hail the Champs - The Schenley High School basketball team, winner of the state championship, was the center of attention at Hotel Webster Hall last Thursday as they were honored at a banquet for their successful season. Members of the team and their coach are shown with championship trophy and new blazers presented to every member of the squad.  Left to right, Jake Williams, Montel Brundage, Marvin Snowden, Coach Willard Fisher, Kenny Durrett, Jim Prince, Ed Gibson and Charles Burley...Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Schenley High School 1966 state championship basketball players holding trophy, from left: Jacob H. Williams Jr., Montel Brundage, Marvin Snowden, coach Willard Fisher, Kenneth "Kenny" Durrett, James "Jimmy" Prince, Edward "Petey" Gibson, and Charles Burley Jr., posed in Hotel Webster Hall
